-- my-ds.page: Adding Footer

In this section, we will learn about adding footer into your pages in
`doc-site`.

`page` component has `show-footer` boolean type property. You can add different
footers using `show-footer: true` property.

We have created few footer components for you. Please, [visit our footer
 package](https://fifthtry.github.io/footer/), you can choose footer of your 
 choice from there. 

In below example we are using `basic-footer` from [footer 
package](https://fifthtry.github.io/footer/).

Add footer dependency inside your `FASTN.ftd` file.

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: fifthtry.github.io/footer

-- ds.markdown:

Now import `fifthtry.github.io/footer` inside your `.ftd` file and apply it to
your `page` component. 

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd
download: footer.ftd

\-- import: fifthtry.github.io/footer

\-- ds.page: Title of the page
show-footer: true

\-- ds.page.footer:

\-- footer.basic-footer:
footer-list: $sitemap.sections
site-logo: https://fastn.com/-/fastn.io/images/fastn.svg
site-url: /
copyright: Copyright Â© 2023 - [FifthTry.com](https://www.fifthtry.com/)

\-- end: ds.page.footer

\-- ds.page.body:
Some page body components and content here

\-- end: ds.page

-- ds.markdown:

Click on download icon of above code-block. `footer.ftd` file will be
downloaded.

Add this file inside your `fastn` project and deploy or run `fastn serve` on
your localhost. Access your localhost in browser
e.g.`http://127.0.0.1:8000/footer/` you will see page with footer.

-- end: my-ds.page